
Task
Determine if a person is an adult.
The person's age is given. Set the result variable to "adult" (if age >= 18) or "not adult" otherwise.
Create a variable age and assign it the value of an arbitrary positive number. 
Create a result variable. Write an if - else command in which check the age >= 18 condition. If the condition is true, assign the value "adult" to the result variable, otherwise assign the value "not adult" to the result variable.

Solution
const age = 10;
let result;
if (age >= 18) {result = 'adult';} else {result = 'not adult';}
